OL,3,CFraudulent gardener scammed elderly
OL,4,Cwidow out of #14,500
OL,6,FAt an earlier hearing Dunleavy, 59,
OL,7,Fhad pleaded guilty to a charge of
OL,8,Fbecoming concerned in a money
OL,9,Flaundering arrangement.
OL,11,FDunleavy admitted setting up the
OL,12,FCheckatrade account and the bank
OL,13,Faccount, which he had suspected was
OL,14,Flikely to be used for criminal
OL,15,Fpurposes.
OL,17,FHe claimed that he had not benefitted
OL,18,Ffrom the offence and was left owing
OL,19,Fmoney to Checkatrade.
