OL,3,CFraudulent gardener scammed elderly
OL,4,Cwidow out of #14,500
OL,6,FHe was sentenced to a nine-month
OL,7,Fprison sentence suspended for two
OL,8,Fyears.
OL,10,FSentencing him Judge Maher told
OL,11,FDunleavy that although there was no
OL,12,Fsuggestion he had been involved in
OL,13,Fcarrying out any work, he had played a
OL,14,Fsignificant role in enabling others to
OL,15,Fdefraud their elderly victim.
OL,17,FHe was also ordered to carry out five
OL,18,Fprobation-supervised rehabilitation
OL,19,Factivity requirement (RAR) days and 40
OL,20,Fhours' unpaid community work.
